1
00:00:37,232 --> 00:00:39,580
Ooh, sweetheart.
Haven't got enough, you didn't order.

2
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:42,379
Well, I've only
just arrived, so tough.

3
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:44,819
Well, what do I do now?

4
00:00:44,820 --> 00:00:47,180
Who is it? Dunno, some bloke.

5
00:00:49,620 --> 00:00:51,859
You going to Slimbo's on Friday?

6
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:53,579
What is it, drinks?

7
00:00:53,580 --> 00:00:55,619
Bit of a pizza, I think.
Might do, yeah.

8
00:00:58,380 --> 00:01:00,059
What's happening there, then?

9
00:01:06,020 --> 00:01:08,143
Move back, if you could, thank you.

10
00:01:08,144 --> 00:01:11,420
Back you go, that's it, back
you go. What's going on?

11
00:01:12,899 --> 00:01:14,779
What's happening?

12
00:01:14,780 --> 00:01:16,420
Buggered if I know.
It's orders from above.

13
00:01:16,421 --> 00:01:19,820
But the body's still in there though, isn't
it? We can't just leave it.

14
00:01:19,821 --> 00:01:21,419
Move back, they said, clear the site.

15
00:01:21,420 --> 00:01:23,059
Special access, they said.

16
00:01:23,060 --> 00:01:24,940
For who? Torchwood.

17
00:01:45,220 --> 00:01:48,100
Who's Torchwood?
Special ops or something.

18
00:01:48,101 --> 00:01:50,299
Is that hot? Er, yeah.

19
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:54,179
They're not allowed in, they could
contaminate the evidence. How come...?

20
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:56,620
Don't ask me,
there's no procedure any more.

21
00:01:56,621 --> 00:01:58,619
It's a fucking disgrace.

22
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,419
There you go. I can taste it.

23
00:02:42,420 --> 00:02:45,179
Oestrogen, definitely oestrogen.

24
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:51,899
You take the Pill, flush it away, it enters
the water cycle, feminises the fish,

25
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:56,579
goes all the way up into the sky, then
falls all the way back down on to me.

26
00:02:56,580 --> 00:03:00,299
Contraceptives in the rain.

27
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:02,139
Love this planet.

28
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:04,700
Still, at least I won't get pregnant.

29
00:03:04,701 --> 00:03:06,500
Never doing that again.

30
00:03:06,501 --> 00:03:08,500
How's it going?

31
00:03:08,501 --> 00:03:12,424
Nothing yet. It's got to connect,
I've just got to feel it.

32
00:03:12,425 --> 00:03:14,819
Hurry up! I'm freezing my arse off.

33
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:19,699
I can't just flick a switch,
it's more like it grants me access.

34
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:24,179
Whatever that means.
It's like... Oh, oh, oh!

35
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:28,059
Positions. If I get punched again,
I'm punching it right back.

36
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:30,220
Just, concentrate. Suzie?

37
00:03:47,180 --> 00:03:49,420
There was... What was?

38
00:03:49,421 --> 00:03:53,019
I was..
Oh, my God, I was going home.

39
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:57,284
Listen to me, we've only got two minutes
so it's important that you listen,

40
00:03:57,285 --> 00:03:58,820
OK? Who are you? Trust me.

41
00:03:58,821 --> 00:04:03,020
You're dead. How am I dead? You were
stabbed. I'm not dead, I can see you.

42
00:04:03,021 --> 00:04:05,141
We've brought you back
but we haven't got long,

43
00:04:05,142 --> 00:04:07,940
I'm sorry but you've got to concentrate,
who did this to you?

44
00:04:07,941 --> 00:04:10,619
What did you see? Why am I dead?
Who attacked you?

45
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:12,899
I don't want to be dead.
Sixty seconds.

46
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:18,939
You've got to think, just focus on me. What
was the last thing you saw? I didn't see...

47
00:04:18,940 --> 00:04:21,420
I don't know.
Who killed you, did you see them?

48
00:04:21,421 --> 00:04:24,380
I don't know.
There was...something behind me.

49
00:04:24,381 --> 00:04:29,580
Police said one stab wound in the back. So
you didn't see anything? No.

50
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:35,539
What happens now?

51
00:04:35,540 --> 00:04:38,899
Thirty seconds. But he didn't
see anyone. Don't waste it.

52
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,540
What else do I say?

53
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,540
What's your name?

54
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:48,100
John. John Tucker. OK, John.

55
00:04:49,939 --> 00:04:53,900
Not long now. Who are you?
Captain Jack Harkness. Tell me...

56
00:04:53,901 --> 00:04:56,379
what was it like when you died?
What did you see?

57
00:04:58,499 --> 00:05:00,059
John.

58
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:02,619
Tell me what you saw.

59
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:04,859
Ten seconds.

60
00:05:04,860 --> 00:05:08,540
Nothing. I saw nothing.

61
00:05:10,180 --> 00:05:12,020
Oh, my God. There's nothing.

62
00:05:18,619 --> 00:05:20,780
Shit.

63
00:05:20,781 --> 00:05:23,699
I said it was stupid, telling
him he was dead. Well, you try it.

64
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:25,780
"Trust me", like that's gonna work.

65
00:05:25,781 --> 00:05:28,090
Told the last corpse he was injured,

66
00:05:28,091 --> 00:05:31,940
he wasted the whole two minutes
screaming for an ambulance.

67
00:05:31,941 --> 00:05:34,940
Maybe there's no right way
of doing it.

68
00:05:34,941 --> 00:05:36,460
What do you think?

69
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:25,460
You still up?

70
00:06:25,461 --> 00:06:26,980
In here.

71
00:06:26,981 --> 00:06:31,380
They said on the news, murder in the
city centre, were you there?

72
00:06:32,459 --> 00:06:34,779
No, I dunno, nothing to do with me.

73
00:06:34,780 --> 00:06:37,979
How come you're still up though?
Banana Boat came round.

74
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:42,340
He was saying he's got plans,
he's off again next summer.

75
00:06:42,341 --> 00:06:44,579
How come you're not pissed then?

76
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:46,579
No, we had a cup of tea.

77
00:06:46,580 --> 00:06:49,459
He's read this thing about diabetes.

78
00:06:49,460 --> 00:06:52,180
Me and him having tea,

79
00:06:52,181 --> 00:06:55,699
that's middle age, that is.
There's some Chinese in the fridge.

80
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:59,899
No, I'm knackered. You coming
to bed? I'll just finish here.

81
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:02,540
This man's found his sister.

82
00:07:04,859 --> 00:07:06,980
I'll see you in a minute.

83
00:07:29,499 --> 00:07:33,539
Von, can you do a search for me?
Oh, join the queue.

84
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:34,724
It's a Captain Jack Harkness.

85
00:07:34,725 --> 00:07:37,420
Could you check him out? I'm busy.
There's proper channels, Gwen.

86
00:07:37,421 --> 00:07:42,980
What sort of Captain? Don't know. Just
Captain. If I've got time. Thanks! If!

87
00:07:42,981 --> 00:07:47,299
Sarah Pallister, 72,
murdered in her front room.

88
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:51,260
Rani Ghosh, 45,
murdered in Robintree Alley.

89
00:07:51,261 --> 00:07:55,899
And now John Tucker, 19,
murdered in Llangyfelach Lane.

90
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:59,097
So far, there's absolutely nothing
linking these three victims,

91
00:07:59,098 --> 00:08:00,620
apart from the way they died.

92
00:08:00,621 --> 00:08:03,140
As far as we can tell,
all with the same weapon.

93
00:08:03,141 --> 00:08:06,380
A blade, approximately eight
inches long, three inches deep.

94
00:08:06,381 --> 00:08:09,509
The women were stabbed from the
front, but Tucker from behind.

95
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:11,579
What does that tell us about the killer?

96
00:08:11,580 --> 00:08:13,179
That he's a coward.

97
00:08:14,740 --> 00:08:18,620
But those people last night, the
people in the car, who were they?

98
00:08:18,621 --> 00:08:21,299
What's Torchwood?
Dunno, special ops.

99
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:22,939
Yeah, but what does that mean?

100
00:08:22,940 --> 00:08:25,600
Bet you ten quid they're DNA specialists,

101
00:08:25,601 --> 00:08:28,780
it's all DNA these days,
like that CSI bollocks.

102
00:08:28,781 --> 00:08:30,739
CSI Cardiff, I'd like to see that.

103
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:33,659
They'd be measuring
the velocity of a kebab.

104
00:08:36,940 --> 00:08:40,019
Thank you(!) Break it up!

105
00:09:44,499 --> 00:09:49,420
Excuse me. It's all sealed off
up there. Who did that?

106
00:09:49,421 --> 00:09:53,339
Thought it was you lot.
But what's it for, what's happened?

107
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:57,140
9am, it was all sealed off, they never
said. Chemicals or something.

108
00:10:08,099 --> 00:10:09,619
Hello?

109
00:10:17,219 --> 00:10:19,580
Sorry, I'm just looking for someone.

110
00:10:31,899 --> 00:10:34,820
Right, yeah. Clever.

111
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:41,099
Anyway, I don't know if you
saw a man come through here -

112
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:46,380
a tall man, in one of those
big sort of military coats.

113
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:58,380
OK. If you could answer?
This is official business.

114
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:02,860
You all right?

115
00:11:06,619 --> 00:11:11,980
That's good.
That's a good mask sort of thing.

116
00:11:11,981 --> 00:11:16,780
Look, I'm sorry if I'm
interrupting something, but...

117
00:11:16,781 --> 00:11:19,340
I think we can stop this now, OK?

118
00:11:19,341 --> 00:11:24,499
It's all very well playing silly
buggers, but I'm busy, all right?

119
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:29,219
Now, I'm looking for a man
in a big grey coat.

120
00:11:31,579 --> 00:11:34,779
I said we can stop being silly.

121
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:37,929
Ah, there you are, I did ask when I saw Dr

122
00:11:37,930 --> 00:11:41,380
Mahib cos I thought it
was him who said about

123
00:11:41,381 --> 00:11:42,429
the police, but he said no,

124
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:45,419
then I said about the chemicals but he
said don't be stupid, what chemicals?

125
00:11:45,420 --> 00:11:48,489
So I don't know, could be anything,
who've you got with you there then?

126
00:11:48,490 --> 00:11:49,700
So much for sealing it off.

127
00:11:49,701 --> 00:11:52,619
Ooh, there's a face!

128
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:58,180
Nice one. Hey, I tell you mate, you should
try plastic surgery. Not on the NHS mind!

129
00:11:58,181 --> 00:12:01,300
You all right? Yeah.

130
00:12:01,301 --> 00:12:04,699
Bloody hell, that is brilliant.

131
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:07,940
That's like, em, Hellraiser.

132
00:12:07,941 --> 00:12:12,580
That's first class, that is. Look at
that, it's just like real teeth.

133
00:12:16,979 --> 00:12:20,019
Go! Go! Go!

134
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:19,060
Registration - Charlie Foxtrot
Zero Six Foxtrot Delta Uniform.

135
00:13:19,061 --> 00:13:21,714
Charlie Foxtrot Zero Six
Foxtrot Delta Uniform.

136
00:13:21,715 --> 00:13:23,860
Hold on. I think Yvonne wants a word.

137
00:13:23,861 --> 00:13:25,940
No sign of a Captain Jack Harkness.

138
00:13:25,941 --> 00:13:28,020
Did you search outside Cardiff?

139
00:13:28,021 --> 00:13:31,580
No, that never occurred to me(!)
Of course I did. I went nationwide.

140
00:13:31,581 --> 00:13:35,544
There's about 15 Jacks and Johns with
that surname, none of them's a captain.

141
00:13:35,545 --> 00:13:36,779
He could've made it up.

142
00:13:36,780 --> 00:13:39,739
The only Captain Jack Harkness
on record was American.

143
00:13:39,740 --> 00:13:44,579
That's it, he's American! Which you forgot
to tell me. So who is he?

144
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:47,500
American volunteer, Royal Air Force,
133 Squadron. Except he disappeared.

145
00:13:47,501 --> 00:13:50,740
Vanished off the records.
Presumed dead. When was that?

146
00:13:50,741 --> 00:13:52,780
1941. At the height of the Blitz.

147
00:13:52,781 --> 00:13:58,099
On the morning of January 21 1941, Captain
Jack Harkness failed to report for duty,

148
00:13:58,100 --> 00:14:00,340
never seen again, till now.

149
00:14:00,341 --> 00:14:03,620
What's going on, Gwen,
you seeing ghosts?

150
00:14:19,419 --> 00:14:21,980
You lot! Oi!

151
00:14:21,981 --> 00:14:23,739
Torchwood!

152
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:25,191
You can't leave that there.

153
00:14:25,192 --> 00:14:28,900
Police. I can see that, love, and
you're still not leaving it there.

154
00:14:31,420 --> 00:14:33,779
I'm talking to you. Excuse me!

155
00:14:33,780 --> 00:14:35,380
Move your bloody car...

156
00:14:45,619 --> 00:14:48,580
Did you get anything
on that registration?

157
00:14:48,581 --> 00:14:50,819
No such number.

158
00:14:50,820 --> 00:14:52,619
What does that mean?

159
00:14:52,620 --> 00:14:54,987
Doesn't exist. Double checked with Swansea,

160
00:14:54,988 --> 00:14:57,740
triple-checked, there's
nothing, no such vehicle.

161
00:14:57,741 --> 00:15:00,860
But Temple's been asking about
you, Gwen. Are you in trouble?

162
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,740
I have walked.

163
00:15:05,741 --> 00:15:08,020
I have bloody walked.

164
00:15:09,980 --> 00:15:12,899
They were here,
and then they were gone.

165
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:16,100
And look, there's nowhere to hide.
They just disappeared.

166
00:15:16,101 --> 00:15:18,860
Temple's not just livid,
he's doing his nut.

167
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:27,579
There was a man, I'm telling you, there was
this porter, he was in a porter's uniform,

168
00:15:27,580 --> 00:15:30,580
and he was killed,
or at least he was injured,

169
00:15:30,581 --> 00:15:32,118
he must've been injured,

170
00:15:32,119 --> 00:15:36,539
right in front of me, this man in
a mask, sort of lashed out, and...

171
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:41,339
And I've told you, all
hospital staff, present and correct.

172
00:15:43,860 --> 00:15:48,460
I saw it. That's it? Gwen, sweetheart,
think about it, what sort of story is that?

173
00:15:49,540 --> 00:15:52,619
You're not well. Come with me.
I'll take you home.

174
00:15:54,380 --> 00:15:57,100
They were here. Come on.

175
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:15,700
Look at me! Hot pot!

176
00:16:15,701 --> 00:16:18,779
Or, as the French call it, ho po.

177
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:22,700
Oh, I should've phoned.
I've got to work.

178
00:16:22,701 --> 00:16:24,699
You should be off sick.

179
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:27,779
I know, but they were short
and there's a match on tonight,

180
00:16:27,780 --> 00:16:30,939
so I said I'd take another shift.
I'm sorry.

181
00:16:30,940 --> 00:16:33,419
Forgive me.

182
00:16:33,420 --> 00:16:37,700
Go on, forgive me. Say you
forgive me, you do, don't you?

183
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:42,340
OK I got to go.

184
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:30,500
Excuse me, Gwen Cooper, CID.

185
00:17:30,501 --> 00:17:32,500
I'm making some enquiries round the Bay.

186
00:17:32,501 --> 00:17:35,500
I need to check some people out
on your list, if that's OK.

187
00:17:35,501 --> 00:17:38,980
I don't suppose you deliver
to a Captain Jack Harkness?

188
00:17:38,981 --> 00:17:41,699
I dunno.
Well, could you have a look?

189
00:17:43,219 --> 00:17:45,100
Nope.

190
00:17:45,101 --> 00:17:47,420
He's not a regular anyway.

191
00:17:47,421 --> 00:17:49,700
J Harkness? Or just Harkness?

192
00:17:56,140 --> 00:17:57,179
No.

193
00:17:57,180 --> 00:18:00,300
OK. Never mind. Thanks anyway.

194
00:18:02,099 --> 00:18:06,314
I don't suppose you've got a Torchwood?
Oh, aye, we do them all the time.

195
00:18:06,315 --> 00:18:07,700
They're good customers.

196
00:18:38,459 --> 00:18:40,545
Oh, hiya. Sorry I'm late.

197
00:18:40,546 --> 00:18:46,139
Someone ordered pizza. Who's it for?
I think it's a...Mr Harkness.

198
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:58,940
Don't keep them waiting.

199
00:21:06,260 --> 00:21:08,140
I can't do this, I'm sorry.

200
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:09,900
I'm rubbish. I give up!

201
00:21:09,901 --> 00:21:14,020
He set me off. Well, that lasted
nought point two seconds.

202
00:21:14,021 --> 00:21:16,780
She's actually carrying pizza!

203
00:21:16,781 --> 00:21:18,147
Come on! She was gonna say,

204
00:21:18,148 --> 00:21:21,740
"Here's your pizza," and I was going
to say, "How much?" and she says,

205
00:21:21,741 --> 00:21:23,939
"Oh, whatever, twenty quid,"

206
00:21:23,940 --> 00:21:28,140
and I say, "Oh, I don't have any
money." I was working on a punchline.

207
00:21:28,141 --> 00:21:31,020
I'd have got there.
But it would've been good!

208
00:21:31,021 --> 00:21:34,340
There's your pizza. I'd better go.
We've gone past that stage.

209
00:21:34,341 --> 00:21:35,965
You must've been freezing out there.

210
00:21:35,966 --> 00:21:38,899
How long were you walking around?
Three hours? You could see me?

211
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:43,540
And before we go any further, who the hell
orders pizza under the name of Torchwood?

212
00:21:43,541 --> 00:21:47,419
Me. I'm sorry. I'm a twat.

213
00:21:47,420 --> 00:21:53,499
That man, at the hospital,
that porter, what happened to him?

214
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:59,180
That was real, wasn't it? He was attacked.
He's dead. But there's no-one gone missing.

215
00:21:59,181 --> 00:22:01,417
We took the body, changed the work rota,

216
00:22:01,418 --> 00:22:04,660
planted a false witness who
saw him leaving the hospital,

217
00:22:04,661 --> 00:22:07,259
giving him an alibi
for the next 48 hours,

218
00:22:07,260 --> 00:22:10,058
so when his body's pulled out of
the docks next Tuesday night,

219
00:22:10,059 --> 00:22:11,819
he's only been missing for three days.

220
00:22:11,820 --> 00:22:15,299
He was murdered? Yes. And you
covered it up? That's my job.

221
00:22:18,060 --> 00:22:21,285
And that other man, John Tucker?
Last night in the alleyway,

222
00:22:21,286 --> 00:22:23,060
I saw you. And what did you see?

223
00:22:23,061 --> 00:22:25,820
You revived him. No.

224
00:22:25,821 --> 00:22:28,739
What did you see?
You resuscitated him.

225
00:22:28,740 --> 00:22:32,459
No, what did you see?

226
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:35,780
You brought him back to life. Yeah.

227
00:22:37,499 --> 00:22:39,260
Who are you?

228
00:22:39,261 --> 00:22:43,980
Torchwood. What's Torchwood?
This is Torchwood.

229
00:22:43,981 --> 00:22:46,900
All around you.

230
00:22:46,901 --> 00:22:51,820
And what happens to me? I'm police.
Constable Gwen Cooper.

231
00:22:51,821 --> 00:22:54,259
You can't do anything.

232
00:22:55,060 --> 00:22:58,420
Right then, PC Cooper...

233
00:23:00,340 --> 00:23:02,700
..d'you want to come see?

234
00:23:02,701 --> 00:23:05,380
See what? You saw the murder.

235
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:08,980
Come and see the murderer.

236
00:23:13,580 --> 00:23:15,859
Go with him.

237
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:24,340
What is Torchwood? Who are you? What is
this place? SCREECHING

238
00:23:24,341 --> 00:23:26,780
What was that? Pterodactyl.

239
00:23:26,781 --> 00:23:29,779
Are you coming?

240
00:23:49,140 --> 00:23:54,299
It's all right -
it's safe, it's sedated.

241
00:23:57,659 --> 00:24:00,020
It's called a Weevil.

242
00:24:00,021 --> 00:24:02,219
Or at least, we call them Weevils.

243
00:24:02,220 --> 00:24:06,100
We don't know their real name, cos they're
