and lie about his death.

267
00:25:42,981 --> 00:25:46,030
OK! Tosh, finish that calibration
tomorrow morning.

268
00:25:46,031 --> 00:25:49,140
Owen, first thing, get a
hold of Chandler and Bell,

269
00:25:49,141 --> 00:25:50,574
cos I think they're lying.

270
00:25:50,575 --> 00:25:54,379
Ianto, if he needs back-up, then you'd
better be on stand-by. Suzie,

271
00:25:54,380 --> 00:25:55,998
I know it's a pain in the ass,

272
00:25:55,999 --> 00:25:59,939
but I need the costing on the glove
research, and you're coming with me.

273
00:26:02,339 --> 00:26:05,620
I'm getting tired of following you.

274
00:26:05,621 --> 00:26:09,420
No you're not, and you never will.

275
00:26:10,940 --> 00:26:14,259
Stand on here. C'mon, next to me.

276
00:26:14,260 --> 00:26:15,540
Good night!

277
00:26:16,699 --> 00:26:20,140
Now, you came in
through the front door.

278
00:26:20,141 --> 00:26:23,020
Let's take the scenic route.

279
00:26:59,180 --> 00:27:03,220
But they can see the lift.

280
00:27:03,221 --> 00:27:06,900
Why aren't they...?

281
00:27:06,901 --> 00:27:10,299
We're right out in the open.
They can see everything!

282
00:27:10,300 --> 00:27:12,680
Do they look like they
can see us? No, but...

283
00:27:12,681 --> 00:27:15,379
Look at us! We couldn't be
any more public! Hello!

284
00:27:15,380 --> 00:27:18,500
Hey, you there, hello!

285
00:27:18,501 --> 00:27:23,739
It's called a perception filter. He can
sort of see us, but we don't quite register.

286
00:27:23,740 --> 00:27:26,500
Just like something
in the corner of your eye.

287
00:27:26,501 --> 00:27:33,539
It only works on this exact spot.
Step off... Hi! Nice night!

288
00:27:33,540 --> 00:27:35,620
And lo, we are perceived.

289
00:27:37,179 --> 00:27:41,540
How does it work? No idea. We know
how to use it, not how it happens.

290
00:27:41,541 --> 00:27:43,454
But if I were to guess,
I'd say that there was

291
00:27:43,455 --> 00:27:45,700
once a dimensionally transcendental
chameleon-circuit

292
00:27:45,701 --> 00:27:48,672
placed right on this spot which welded its

293
00:27:48,673 --> 00:27:52,139
perception properties to
a spatio-temporal rift.

294
00:27:52,140 --> 00:27:54,340
But that sounds kind of ridiculous.

295
00:27:54,341 --> 00:27:57,006
"Invisible lift" has got
more of a ring to it.

296
00:27:57,007 --> 00:28:00,019
But if no-one can see it
when the lift's coming up,

297
00:28:00,020 --> 00:28:03,299
there's a bloody big hole in
the floor, don't people fall in?

298
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:05,540
That is so Welsh. What is?

299
00:28:05,541 --> 00:28:08,939
I show you something fantastic -
you find fault.

300
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:34,899
I just don't understand...
I tell you what I don't understand.

301
00:28:34,900 --> 00:28:36,500
You're gonna rattle on with that,

302
00:28:36,501 --> 00:28:39,460
"How can this be true?" What's
it gonna take for you people?

303
00:28:39,461 --> 00:28:41,019
If you want evidence of aliens,

304
00:28:41,020 --> 00:28:44,539
how about that great spaceship hovering
over London on Christmas Day?

305
00:28:44,540 --> 00:28:47,459
What about the battle of Canary
Wharf? A Cyberman in every home!

306
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:50,151
My boyfriend says it's like
a sort of terrorism.

307
00:28:50,152 --> 00:28:52,619
Like they put drugs in the water supplies -

308
00:28:52,620 --> 00:28:56,940
psychotropic drugs, causing
mass hallucinations and stuff.

309
00:28:56,941 --> 00:29:00,460
Yeah, well your boyfriend's stupid.
Oh, you've met him?

310
00:29:06,580 --> 00:29:10,139
So...you catch aliens?

311
00:29:10,140 --> 00:29:12,299
Yup. You catch aliens for a living?

312
00:29:12,300 --> 00:29:15,740
Yes, we do. You're an alien-catcher?
Yes, I am. Caught any good aliens?

313
00:29:15,741 --> 00:29:18,299
Tons of 'em! That's hell of a job.
Sure is.

314
00:29:22,060 --> 00:29:23,860
This is so weird.

315
00:29:25,900 --> 00:29:31,619
And who are you, then?
Captain Jack Harkness.

316
00:29:31,620 --> 00:29:36,539
I did some research and there's only one
Captain Jack Harkness on record.

317
00:29:36,540 --> 00:29:43,699
And he disappeared in 1941. Well...
that couldn't be me...could it?

318
00:29:47,059 --> 00:29:49,859
We don't just catch aliens.

319
00:29:49,860 --> 00:29:52,180
We scavenge the stuff
they leave behind.

320
00:29:52,181 --> 00:29:55,660
Find ways of using it.
Arming the human race for the future.

321
00:29:55,661 --> 00:29:59,431
The twenty-first century is when it all
changes, and you've got to be ready.

322
00:29:59,432 --> 00:30:00,820
But who's in charge of you?

323
00:30:00,821 --> 00:30:05,260
We're separate from the government. Outside
the police. Beyond the United Nations.

324
00:30:05,261 --> 00:30:07,820
Cos if one power got hold of this stuff,

325
00:30:07,821 --> 00:30:11,660
they could use it for their own
purposes. But so could you.

326
00:30:11,661 --> 00:30:16,859
All alien technology stays on the base.
No-one's allowed to take anything outside.

327
00:30:52,619 --> 00:30:56,459
So go on, then. How the hell
did you end up in Cardiff?

328
00:30:56,460 --> 00:31:02,339
This is Torchwood Three. Torchwood One was
London, destroyed in the battle.

329
00:31:02,340 --> 00:31:07,419
Torchwood Two is an office
in Glasgow, very strange man.

330
00:31:07,420 --> 00:31:08,756
Torchwood three, Cardiff.

331
00:31:08,757 --> 00:31:12,180
Torchwood Four's kinda gone missing,
but we'll find it one day.

332
00:31:12,181 --> 00:31:14,139
So you just fancied Cardiff?

333
00:31:14,140 --> 00:31:18,139
There's a rift in space and time
running right through the city.

334
00:31:18,140 --> 00:31:22,499
The Weevils didn't come in a
spaceship. They just slip through.

335
00:31:22,500 --> 00:31:24,740
All sorts of things
get washed up here.

336
00:31:24,741 --> 00:31:29,143
Creatures, timeshifts, space junk,
debris, flotsam and jetsam.

337
00:31:29,144 --> 00:31:31,060
Sounds like Cardiff, yeah.

338
00:31:31,061 --> 00:31:33,700
Hey, don't knock it, I'm a citizen.

339
00:31:33,701 --> 00:31:35,860
But where are you from?

340
00:31:35,861 --> 00:31:39,340
All sorts of places.

341
00:31:39,341 --> 00:31:41,620
Thing is, we could liaise on this...

342
00:31:41,621 --> 00:31:46,660
the serial killer. I could be like
your liaison with the police.

343
00:31:46,661 --> 00:31:49,179
Right, I can see the mistake.

344
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:53,219
You think because we showed up
we're out to catch the killer.

345
00:31:53,220 --> 00:31:58,019
Sorry. Nothing to do with us. Then what
were you doing there? Testing the glove.

346
00:31:59,020 --> 00:32:02,899
We need murder victims, simple as that. The
glove only works on the recently deceased,

347
00:32:02,900 --> 00:32:05,251
and the more violent the trauma,
the stronger the resurrection.

348
00:32:05,252 --> 00:32:06,259
All we need is fresh meat.

349
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:07,840
No, you were asking that man,

350
00:32:07,841 --> 00:32:11,220
John Tucker, I saw you, you were
asking him about his killer.

351
00:32:11,221 --> 00:32:12,361
He'd just been murdered,

352
00:32:12,362 --> 00:32:15,500
what else are you gonna ask? You
could get an ID. You could help.

353
00:32:15,501 --> 00:32:20,460
We're busy. And your work is more
important? Now you've got it.

354
00:32:20,461 --> 00:32:21,750
Well, that's tough shit.

355
00:32:21,751 --> 00:32:25,620
Cos if you let me go, then I have a
duty, cos that glove could help us.

356
00:32:27,340 --> 00:32:30,539
If you remember. What d'you mean?

357
00:32:30,540 --> 00:32:32,740
How's your drink?

358
00:32:37,140 --> 00:32:42,340
Have you poisoned me? Don't be so
dramatic. It's an amnesia pill.

359
00:32:42,341 --> 00:32:45,339
My own recipe, with a touch
of denial and a dash of retcon.

360
00:32:45,340 --> 00:32:48,699
Wake up tomorrow morning, you'll have
forgotten everything about Torchwood.

361
00:32:48,700 --> 00:32:50,740
Worse still,
you'll have forgotten me...

362
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:55,219
..which is kind of tragic.

363
00:33:01,580 --> 00:33:04,219
Don't think you can fight it
by staying awake.

364
00:33:04,220 --> 00:33:06,340
I mixed in a little
bit of sedative too.

365
00:33:06,341 --> 00:33:10,939
Then I'll tell someone! D'you really
want us to come and find them too?

366
00:33:10,940 --> 00:33:13,900
You bastard. Language!

367
00:33:13,901 --> 00:33:16,300
Nice knowing you, Gwen Cooper.

368
00:34:12,299 --> 00:34:14,339
Hello. All right?

369
00:34:14,340 --> 00:34:20,459
You having a good time? I was.
Can I buy you a drink?

370
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:23,259
No, thanks, I'm fine.

371
00:34:25,379 --> 00:34:26,980
Am I wasting my time?

372
00:34:26,981 --> 00:34:30,020
I dunno, are you?

373
00:34:32,620 --> 00:34:35,246
I've got to be up early and
I've got hell of a day

374
00:34:35,247 --> 00:34:37,979
tomorrow and I can't be bothered
with all the chat.

375
00:34:44,380 --> 00:34:48,059
So...do you want a drink or what?

376
00:34:57,299 --> 00:35:03,020
Bloody hell fire. You're coming
home with me, you are. Right now!

377
00:36:12,979 --> 00:36:18,380
Oi, you bastard, come here! Linda, what the
fuck do you think you are doing?!

378
00:36:18,381 --> 00:36:21,179
I'm taking him home
and I'm having him, now piss off!

379
00:36:21,180 --> 00:36:24,056
What the fuck d'you think you're
doing with my girlfriend? Hey,

380
00:36:24,057 --> 00:36:25,700
she was on her own. She never said.

381
00:36:25,701 --> 00:36:29,380
You fucking tosser.
Colin, button it, he's mine.

382
00:36:29,381 --> 00:36:33,551
Do you want to have a go? You want to
have a go? Come on then mate! Well,

383
00:36:33,552 --> 00:36:34,979
