384
00:36:41,299 --> 00:36:44,020
I am so having you.

385
00:36:44,021 --> 00:36:46,540
I'm having him first! Taxi!

386
00:38:23,699 --> 00:38:28,460
Did you get pissed? No.

387
00:38:28,461 --> 00:38:31,579
What time is it?

388
00:38:31,580 --> 00:38:33,220
Seven thirty.

389
00:38:33,221 --> 00:38:37,780
You said you were working
last night. I was.

390
00:38:37,781 --> 00:38:40,259
Then how come
you fell asleep in here?

391
00:38:40,260 --> 00:38:44,300
I haven't, I was...typing.

392
00:38:44,301 --> 00:38:46,619
That is work.

393
00:38:46,620 --> 00:38:49,300
I'm not having a go, I'm just saying.

394
00:38:49,301 --> 00:38:53,219
Not exactly clever going out on the lash
when you've just had a bang on the head.

395
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:57,619
I hope you didn't drive in that
state. Who were you with? Diane?

396
00:38:57,620 --> 00:39:00,180
Must've been. Yeah.

397
00:39:05,179 --> 00:39:08,179
Have any luck? With what?

398
00:39:08,180 --> 00:39:10,379
Captain Jack Harkness.

399
00:39:10,380 --> 00:39:12,620
How d'you mean? Who's he? Oh,

400
00:39:12,621 --> 00:39:17,179
well don't worry about me, just
go ahead, wasting my time.

401
00:39:29,019 --> 00:39:32,540
Aye, aye. Come to see
where the real work's done?

402
00:39:32,541 --> 00:39:37,580
Yes, sir, that's right, sir.
How's it going? Sod all.

403
00:39:41,819 --> 00:39:48,340
Is that the murder weapon? Clever, mind,
they worked it all out on a computer.

404
00:39:48,341 --> 00:39:53,900
Took measurements from the stab wounds,
calculated the shape of the blade and stuff,

405
00:39:53,901 --> 00:39:57,100
even those prongs -
I don't know how they do it.

406
00:39:57,101 --> 00:39:59,859
Nasty-looking beast, though.

407
00:39:59,860 --> 00:40:05,740
D'you recognise it? No. We're trying to
trace it. Can't be that many of 'em.

408
00:40:05,741 --> 00:40:08,317
Sort of ornamental. We're checking the CDE

409
00:40:08,318 --> 00:40:11,140
logs with customs in case
it's been imported.

410
00:40:11,141 --> 00:40:13,300
Find the knife,
we might find the killer.

411
00:40:13,301 --> 00:40:18,900
Anyway, if it rings any bells,
give's a shout. Yeah. Thanks.

412
00:40:33,100 --> 00:40:35,539
..I said to Geoff,
it's not demotion being put in goal,

413
00:40:35,540 --> 00:40:38,500
it's vital,
but was he having any of it?

414
00:40:38,501 --> 00:40:42,179
He's off and moaning, says, who
books the ground, who pays the subs?

415
00:40:42,180 --> 00:40:45,539
And all the time,
he's wheezing away,

416
00:40:45,540 --> 00:40:47,819
and I'm like, Geoff,
you're proving my point mate...

417
00:40:47,820 --> 00:40:51,811
"You never come down, you're
in charge of transport.

418
00:40:51,812 --> 00:40:55,419
" I said, "Mam, I can't
go hopping on a truck!"

419
00:40:55,420 --> 00:41:00,899
All that Christmas stuff, all over again, I
was like, for God's sake, leave it...

420
00:43:19,380 --> 00:43:22,700
Hello again. You were right.

421
00:43:22,701 --> 00:43:28,379
You told Jack we should liaise with the
police. I was the only one who bothered.

422
00:43:28,380 --> 00:43:31,859
So I was the only one
who saw the report.

423
00:43:34,260 --> 00:43:38,860
They got a good likeness.
I'm arresting you for...

424
00:43:38,861 --> 00:43:41,260
How do I know you? I thought you saw it.

425
00:43:41,261 --> 00:43:44,859
And that can trip the amnesia,
one image, if you're clever.

426
00:43:44,860 --> 00:43:47,500
He said you were good.

427
00:43:47,501 --> 00:43:52,020
Anyway. It's not much good
now, I can't really...

428
00:43:52,021 --> 00:43:57,139
But you're gonna put up a fight.
So I've got...

429
00:43:57,140 --> 00:43:59,339
Um. Hold on. Sorry.

430
00:44:03,820 --> 00:44:05,659
There. That's better.

431
00:44:05,660 --> 00:44:09,300
Put it down. You had to come back.
Put down the gun.

432
00:44:09,301 --> 00:44:14,699
You're the only one who can make the link.
Well, the only one in public.

433
00:44:14,700 --> 00:44:19,820
Torchwood's gonna find out
by morning, but I'll be gone.

434
00:44:19,821 --> 00:44:22,940
I don't know where. Far away.

435
00:44:22,941 --> 00:44:25,300
What am I gonna do?

436
00:44:26,819 --> 00:44:29,540
I loved this job. I really loved it.

437
00:44:29,541 --> 00:44:33,539
And now I've got to run.

438
00:44:33,540 --> 00:44:36,499
Oh, Christ.

439
00:44:36,500 --> 00:44:39,885
How can you do any other job
after this one? Please.

440
00:44:39,886 --> 00:44:42,619
Put down the gun. Cos it gets inside you.

441
00:44:42,620 --> 00:44:46,420
You do this job for long
enough, and you end up thinking,

442
00:44:46,421 --> 00:44:51,140
"How come we get all
the Weevils and bollocks and shit?"

443
00:44:51,141 --> 00:44:54,100
Is that what alien life is? Filth?

444
00:44:54,101 --> 00:44:58,939
But maybe there's better stuff
out there, brilliant stuff,

445
00:44:58,940 --> 00:45:01,060
beautiful stuff. Just...

446
00:45:01,061 --> 00:45:04,059
they don't come here.

447
00:45:06,020 --> 00:45:09,419
This planet's so dirty,
that's all we get - the shit.

448
00:45:09,420 --> 00:45:14,860
I don't know what you're talking
about. I wish I could forget.

449
00:45:14,861 --> 00:45:19,699
Why did you kill those people?
For the glove. Stay where you are.

450
00:45:19,700 --> 00:45:22,859
I needed the bodies.
That's how it works. Violent death.

451
00:45:22,860 --> 00:45:24,699
And it was so easy. To bring them back,

452
00:45:24,700 --> 00:45:27,859
I'd position myself behind the head,
so they'd never see me twice.

453
00:45:27,860 --> 00:45:31,300
You killed three people.
It was the only way.

454
00:45:31,301 --> 00:45:36,059
The more I use the glove, the more I
control it. I don't understand, what glove?

455
00:45:36,060 --> 00:45:39,460
If I can get enough practice,
then think what that glove could do.

456
00:45:39,461 --> 00:45:41,039
If I could get it work all the time,

457
00:45:41,040 --> 00:45:43,979
on anything, beyond the two minutes,
if it could work permanently,

458
00:45:43,980 --> 00:45:45,659
it could resurrect.

459
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:49,580
Resurrection on demand for
the whole world, isn't that good?

460
00:45:49,581 --> 00:45:54,859
Isn't it though? Well, that's what I've
been working for, all day and all night.

461
00:45:54,860 --> 00:45:58,700
The rest of them
go swanning about, but I'm working.

462
00:45:58,701 --> 00:46:03,379
You've got to get inside this stuff.
Surrender yourself to it.

463
00:46:03,380 --> 00:46:05,418
I did, with the knife, and the glove,

464
00:46:05,419 --> 00:46:08,780
and that's why the perception
filter isn't gonna work on me.

465
00:46:12,219 --> 00:46:14,980
Where did he come from?

